dismissalText.commentary: Peter Chase c & b Rashid Khan 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: gone first ball! Chase has nothing to lose and he goes for a big hit down the ground. The ball goes high, high in the air, Chase knows that he is done for and doesn't even look as Rashid takes the catch. Afghanistan wins!

dismissalText.commentary: Peter Chase c & b Rashid Khan 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

commentTextItems.html: gone first ball! Chase has nothing to lose and he goes for a big hit down the ground. The ball goes high, high in the air, Chase knows that he is done for and doesn't even look as Rashid takes the catch. Afghanistan wins!

commentPostTextItems.html: It's a comfortable victory in the end for Afghanistan, the first eight Irish Batsman got into double figures yet apart from Balbirnie none of them could push on.
You could tell that as soon as Balbirnie was out, that the momentum in the innings dropped. With only one boundary hit in the last 16 overs, they were always going to fall short.
Two run outs definitely didn't help the cause and with the wickets spread out between the bowlers, it was an all around effort from the Afghan team.

So Afghanistan go one nil up in the series, luckily we don't have long to wait until the second game. I hope that you will be able to join me then, until then this is Justin saying godd night from Stormont.

dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson b Rashid Khan 38 (50b 0x4 1x6 70m) SR: 76

commentTextItems.html: well he hits them this time! Wilson tres to sweep a good length ball into the legside, think that it did him for pace and the stumps are knocked over.
hits the pad and Wilson calls for the run, Rashid picks up the ball and throws at the non-strikers end. Couls have been close if he had hit the stumps.
clips the ball into the on-side and then ambles down the other end, not too sure about the running although I guess when you are that tall it doesn't take long to get down the other end!

milestones.description: Rahmat Shah has scored 14 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AFG breaking Shahzad's record
Gulbadin Naib has broken the record for most ducks (5) in ODIs for AFG, going past Dawlat Zadran's 5
Balbirnie has broken the record for most catches in an innings (4) in ODIs for IRE, going past Eoin Morgan's 3
